# MS DevX — Cursor AI Rules

## Project identity
- Brand: MS DevX | Domain: msdevx.com | Tools: tools.marth.systems
- Tagline: "Build smarter. Ship faster."

## Stack — never deviate
- Next.js 14+ App Router (never Pages Router)
- TypeScript strict mode — no `any`, no implicit types
- Tailwind CSS only — no CSS modules, no styled-components, no inline style objects unless unavoidable
- shadcn/ui for all UI primitives
- Lucide React for all icons — never use emoji as icons
- Framer Motion for animations
- React Hook Form + Zod for every form
- next-themes for dark/light mode

## Architecture rules
- Server Components by default — add "use client" only when needed (forms, animations, hooks)
- All page data comes from /content/data JSON files or MDX — never hardcode content in components
- All site config (name, nav, social links, colors) lives in /lib/constants.ts only
- All TypeScript interfaces live in /lib/types.ts only — never define types inline in components
- All utility functions live in /lib/utils.ts
- Components never fetch data — pass data as props from page/layout Server Components

## File & folder naming
- Components: PascalCase (HeroSection.tsx, NavBar.tsx)
- Files/folders: kebab-case (hero-section.tsx is wrong — use HeroSection.tsx)
- Hooks: camelCase starting with "use" (useDebounce.ts)
- Data files: camelCase (apps.json, toolsList.json)

## Component rules
- Every component must have a typed Props interface above the function
- No default exports from /lib files — named exports only
- Components in /sections are page-section-level, not reusable atoms
- Components in /shared are reusable across sections and pages
- Components in /ui are shadcn primitives only — never modify them

## Styling rules
- Use brand color tokens from tailwind.config.ts: navy, electricBlue, skyBlue, teal, offwhite, ink
- Dark mode: use dark: Tailwind prefix — CSS variables defined in globals.css
- Consistent card style: rounded-2xl border border-border p-6 bg-card
- Focus states required on all interactive elements (focus-visible:ring-2)
- No hardcoded hex colors in JSX — always use Tailwind classes

## Code quality
- No console.log in committed code
- No TODO comments left in generated code — complete every task fully
- All next/image usages must include width, height, and alt
- All external links: target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
- Loading and error states required for any async operation
- Every page needs generateMetadata() export

## When modifying existing files
- Read the full file before editing
- Preserve all existing imports
- Never remove code that isn't directly related to the current task
- Add new components at the bottom of their section, never in the middle